<h1>Problem 486 - 2012 IMOSL, G3, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>In an acute triangle \(ABC\) the points \(D,E\) and \(F\) are the feet of the altitudes through \(A,B\) and \(C\) respectively. The incenters of the triangles \(AEF\) and \(BDF\) are \(I_1\) and \(I_2\) respectively; the circumcenters of the triangles \(ACI_1\) and \(BCI_2\) are \(O_1\) and \(O_2\) respectively. Prove that \(I_1I_2\) and \(O_1O_2\) are parallel.</p>
